  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Neither side had anything to say\ntoday regarding the plans agreed\nupon for promoting the settlement.\n\n\nHowever, 1t Is understood that a\ncommittee was appointed to confer\nwith the chamber Of commerce on\nsome strike settlement plan.\n\n\nA plan was suggested during the\ndiscussion before the carpenters, for\nthe appointment Of . general board\nOf arbitration after the settlement Of\nthe millworkers' strike. Before this\nboard must come every grievance be-\ntween capital and labor before any\nstrike can occur.\n\n\nThe scheme was approved by both\nsides."
